Ballast 1.0 command line version - Feb 2000
===========================================

################################################################################
Installation
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1) Download the file ballast.tar.Z

2) Extract the source code from the compressed tar file:

	zcat ballast.tar.Z | tar -xvf -


3) Edit the line specifying the HELPDIR variable in makefile:

	HELPDIR    =  /us1/user/ballast

   Replace the current value by the directory where you intend to leave the
   help file ballast.hlp.


4) Build the executables:

	make

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Note: In order to optimise portability the compilation has not been optimised
      for speed. The performance should be better if you optimise compilation
      for your site.




################################################################################
Usage       
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

You may now run Ballast:

	ballast -p xxxxx.blastp -n xxxxx.tblastn -o yyyyyy

where:
   xxxxx.blastp is the result file from a BlastP search you have performed earlier

   xxxxx.tblastn (optional) is the result file from a TBlastN search you have 
		 performed earlier with the SAME QUERY SEQUENCE as the BlastP search.

   yyyyyy is the file name for your Ballast results. All files produced by Ballast
          will have this name followed by different extensions.



Ballast can read Blast results from the following source:

	- blastall (gapped blast program)
	- GCG blast programs
	- NCBI Blast mail server

Ballast cannot read the HTML output from the NCBI Blast web server.

Examples of Blast results files are included in the distribution:

	SYY_HAEIN.blastp
	SYY_HAEIN.tblastn
	SYY_HAEIN.ncbi_mail_blastp


